<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3735] JSON protocol left in incorrect state when an exception is thrown during read or write operations</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3735</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The JSON context stack may be left in an incorrect state when an exception is thrown during read or write operations. This leads to further errors while writing/reading the NEXT message, because incorrect characters may be written or expected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1473&quot; title=&quot;JSON context stack may be left in an incorrect state when an exception is thrown during read or write operations&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-1473&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-1473&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, but there is an additional issue in that the bufio.Writer needs to be reset if an error occurs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
